        ".  Eisenstein began his career as a theorist in 1923,  by writing The Montage of Attractions for art journal  LEF .  His first film,  Glumovs Diary  , was also made in that same year with ": null
    },
    {
        "Dziga Vertov": "Dziga Vertov"
    },
    {
        " hired initially as an instructor         Strike  was Eisensteins first full-length feature film.  Battleship Potemkin  was critically acclaimed worldwide. Mostly owing to this international renown, he was then able to direct  October   as part of a grand tenth anniversary celebration of the ": null
