        " where he had taught earlier, and in 1933 and 1934 was in charge of writing the curriculum.      In 1935, Eisenstein was assigned another project,  Bezhin Meadow , but it appears the film was afflicted with many of the same problems as ¡Que viva México!. Eisenstein unilaterally decided to film two versions of the scenario, one for adult viewers and one for children; failed to define a clear shooting schedule; and shot film prodigiously, resulting in cost overruns and missed deadlines. ": null
    },
